{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dc0a4a15-184d-4201-b52a-2267e1abd0b3","content":"Yes, you'll hit **framework compatibility issues**. MSTest v3 dropped support for older target frameworks. Here's your situation:\n\n| Target | MSTest v3 Compatible? |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Dropped — requires `net6.0`+ |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Dropped — requires `net6.0`+ |\n\n**To migrate**, you'd need to update your TFMs (e.g., replace `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` with `net6.0` or later). MSTest v3 also consolidates packages into a single `MSTest` metapackage, replacing the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` references.\n\nWould you like me to update the project file for the migration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a9fc38fc-2c97-43a6-bdb7-f53f3b2099b0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is targeting `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. MSTest v3 dropped support for older frameworks. Let me think about what I know:\n\nMSTest v3 requires:\n- .NET 6.0 or later (for .NET Core/5+)\n- .NET Framework 4.6.2 or later\n\nSo the compatibility issues are:\n1. `net5.0` - .NET 5.0 is out of support and MSTest v3 dropped support for it. They'd need to move to `net6.0` or later.\n\n\n2. `netcoreapp3.1` - .NET Core 3.1 is also out of support and MSTest v3 dropped support for it, so they'd need to upgrade to `net6.0` or later as well.\n3. `net462` - .NET Framework 4.6.2 is actually supported by MSTest v3.\n\nOne more thing to note: MSTest v3 consolidated the packages into a single `MSTest` meta-package instead of requiring separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages.","outputTokens":493,"requestId":"E3CC:2B8350:B68EB5:D047CA:6A053C3A"},"id":"08cb7f65-a072-433a-a6a0-f9f7b895cd35","timestamp":"2026-05-14T03:06:44.924Z","parentId":"fffe4860-ac27-47ab-ab81-8d7b5981030f"}
